racting but integrable\n(supersymmetric) CFTs in 4d. We also discuss the corresponding picture in AdS_4\nwhere the 3d conformal group Sp(4,R) admits only two massless representations\n(minreps), namely the scalar and spinor singletons.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Dec 2013 18:22:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 7 Jan 2014 16:59:33 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 27 Oct 2014 19:03:02 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 4 Mar 2015 19:09:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-03-05"}
